# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Purpose (this file is NOT loaded by Vite — documentation only).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Monorepo root .gitignore ignores `.env` and `.env.*.local`, so clones do not ship
# a personal env file by default. This example lists the vars `docs/web/vite.config.ts`
# reads via `loadEnv` + `process.env`: names, format (no trailing slash on origin),
# and placeholders for forks (OWNER / REPO). The real upstream default lives in the
# versioned `.env.production`; CI may still override DOC_SITE_ORIGIN in the workflow.
# See `docs/monorepo-desarrollo.md` → Publishing docs/web → DOC_SITE_ORIGIN row.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Copy to `.env.production` / `.env.development`, or export before `vite build`.
# Either name works: DOC_SITE_ORIGIN (preferred) or DOCS_SITE_ORIGIN.

DOC_SITE_ORIGIN=https://OWNER.github.io/REPO

# Optional — GitHub Pages project site (leading + trailing slashes). Omit locally for dev (base `/`).
# DOCS_SITE_BASE=/REPO/

# Deezer-backed table on prod: GitHub Actions should set secrets.VITE_DEEZER_HTTP_BASE (Worker URL).
# If unset, the SPA still targets api.deezer.com but the browser blocks it (CORS) until this is set.
# Local `vite build`: export or add to `.env.production.local` with your Worker URL, or use `npm run dev` (Vite proxy).
# Deploy relay: docs/web/edge/deezer-proxy/README.md (no trailing slash on URL).
# VITE_DEEZER_HTTP_BASE=https://abey-docs-deezer-proxy.ACCOUNT.workers.dev
